Create a ghost recipe in the crafting grid and add the required materials below it to get it working. This process can be automated with rats transporting and gathering items or the use of hoppers and other modded pipes.

block.rats.rat_quarry.desc1: Set quarry rats to 'Harvest' then assign this block as their deposit position with a cheese staff
block.rats.rat_trap.jei_desc: Place any food item rats will eat in the rat trap to attract wild rats. When they die inside the trap, it needs to be reset. Right click the trap or power it with redstone to reset it.
block.rats.rat_tube.desc0: Right click to place Rat Tube
block.rats.rat_tube.desc1: Right click Rat Tube to create an entrance
block.rats.rat_tube.desc2: Rats will only go inside Rat Tubes that have entrances
block.rats.trash_can.desc0: Right click with an empty hand to open or close
block.rats.trash_can.desc1: Right click with blocks in hand to throw them away

entity.rats.dutchrat.daytime: The Flying Dutchrat can only manifest at night

entity.rats.neo_ratlantean.ratlantis: The vial had no effect on this beast here
entity.rats.rat.command.follow.desc: The rat will follow its owner.
entity.rats.rat.command.gather.desc: The rat will search the area for dropped items (craft whitelist or blacklist upgrades to limit what they pick up). You can use a §6Cheese Staff§r to set a deposit inventory.
entity.rats.rat.command.harvest.desc: The rat will search for mature crops nearby to harvest. You can use a §6Cheese Staff§r to set a deposit inventory where it will drop off any crops it collects. Many upgrades will repurpose this command to allow rats to perform various jobs, such as chopping down trees or breeding animals.
entity.rats.rat.command.hunt.desc: When given a Mob Filter upgrade, the rat will kill all mobs it lists. The rat will also place their remains in a deposit container, if assigned one. Use the §6Cheese Staff§r to set a deposit inventory.
entity.rats.rat.command.patrol.desc: The rat will patrol a set path and fight any monsters it encounters. Right-click the rat with a §6Patrol Staff§r to bind it and right-click any blocks with the staff to add points to patrol along.
entity.rats.rat.command.sit.desc: The rat will sit down and not move.
entity.rats.rat.command.transport.desc: Interacting with a rat with a §6Cheese Staff§r will bind it to the rat. Clicking on a block with an inventory will open a GUI to mark that inventory for the rat to take from/deposit items into. Once the rat has a marked deposit inventory and pickup inventory, it will transport items from one to the other.
entity.rats.rat.command.wander.desc: The rat will move around similar to wild behavior.
entity.rats.rat.dismount: Sneak and punch air to remove rats from shoulder
entity.rats.rat.griefing: NOTICE: this world has Mob Griefing turned off. Rats may not work as expected! Tamed rats will not be able to perform many tasks you would normally expect them to because of this.\nTo fix this, all you need to do is enable the mob griefing gamerule.\nThis message will not appear again.
entity.rats.rat_baron.ratlantis: The siren is unable to bring forth anyone from this world
entity.rats.ratlantean_automaton.ratlant: This machine cannot properly function in this world

item.rats.ratlantis_disabled.desc0: Ratlantis content is disabled in this world.
item.rats.ratlantis_disabled.desc1: None of the items, blocks, or entities from ratlantis can be obtained legitimately in survival.
item.rats.ratlantis_disabled.desc2: If you would like to have Ratlantis related content in your world make sure to enable the builtin datapack on world creation or turn the 'ratlantisEnabledByDefault' config option to true.
item.rats.ratlantis_pickaxe.desc1: Mining stone blocks will not damage this tool.
item.rats.ratlantis_shovel.desc1: Mining sand blocks will not damage this tool.
item.rats.ratlantis_sword.desc1: Each attack summons a spectral rat that deals an additional 6 damage.
item.rats.rattling_gun.desc: Place a rat on the gunner's seat by right clicking with a rat on your shoulder
item.rats.staff.no_rat: Staff is not bound to any rat
item.rats.vial_of_sentience.desc: A serum that can, §lin theory§r§7, reverse the de-evolution of a Ratlantean.
pack.rats.ratlantis: Enables Ratlantis and all Ratlantis related features
